Kyoji Horiguchi is by far the more skilled fighter in this match.  Manel Kape is also a disgusting human being.

[Predictions]

@battousai when has Kyoji been considered the uncrowned featherweight champion considering he's been flyweight and sometimes bantamweight.

I'm hoping that he schools Kape again. I still have memories of the Mokaev fight, considering they kept trying to fight in the hotel and everywhere else except for the cage. Well they were still aggressive until the commission and camera guys got out the cage. Granted, he did better than I expected against Royval, but I was expecting Royval to win

@Grogers70426
Kyoji has only lost once at flyweight ever and it was to Mighty Mouse. Thats why I say hes kind of the uncrowned king of that weight class right now. Hes technically on a 5 fight win streak in the UFC and hasnt lost overall in 3 years. Hes as legit a contender as anybody and if he beats Kape again he will be the #1 contender no questions asked.

The only arguement I see for Kape is this rematch being at 125lbs somehow being an advantage, which Im not sure is sound but it's the only variable that's different. I say this as someone who acknowledges both guys are better than the fist time they fought. I just think Kyoji is still the more complete fighter. Its why he won the first time and its why I think he wins again.

@Spockling
Patchy Mix is gigantic compared to Kyoji and is a respectable loss. Kyoji fought Patchy when he was at his peak, not the version everyone is watching struggle lately.

Kyoji was also beating the breaks off of Sergio Pettis before he got caught in their first fight but then he got his revenge in the rematch.
